[409.927684, "o", "...skipping...\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[7mHISTORY\u001b[27m\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       When  the \u001b[1m-o\u001b[0m \u001b[1mhistory\u001b[0m option to the \u001b[1mset\u001b[0m builtin is en‐\u001b[m\r\n       abled, the shell provides access to the \u001b[4mcommand\u001b[24m  \u001b[4mhis‐\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[4mtory\u001b[24m,  the  list  of  commands previously typed.  The\u001b[m\r\n       value of the \u001b[1mHISTSIZE\u001b[0m variable is used as the  number\u001b[m\r\n       of  commands  to save in a history list.  The text of\u001b[m\r\n       the last \u001b[1mHISTSIZE\u001b[0m commands (default  500)  is  saved.\u001b[m\r\n       The  shell  stores  each  command in the history list\u001b[m\r\n       prior to parameter and variable expansion (see \u001b[1mEXPAN‐\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mSION\u001b[0m above) but after history expansion is performed,\u001b[m\r\n       subject to the values of the shell variables  \u001b[1mHISTIG‐\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mNORE\u001b[0m and \u001b[1mHISTCONTROL\u001b[0m.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       On  startup, the history is initialized from the file\u001b[m\r\n       named by the variable \u001b[1mHISTFILE\u001b[0m (default  \u001b[4m~/.bash_his‐\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[4mtory\u001b[24m).   Th"]
[409.927726, "o", "e  file  named by the value of \u001b[1mHISTFILE\u001b[0m is\u001b[m\r\n       truncated, if necessary, to contain no more than  the\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7manual page bash(1) line 5415 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
